    "faq": {
      "type": "brand-faq",
      "blocks": {
        "faq_1": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Did Bahco really invent the adjustable wrench?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. <strong>Johan Petter Johansson</strong>, founder of the company that became Bahco, patented the modern adjustable wrench in <strong>1892</strong> in Enk\u00f6ping, Sweden. The basic jaw mechanism he invented remains fundamentally unchanged today. Bahco has sold over 100 million adjustable wrenches worldwide since then.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_2": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What is Bahco ERGO technology?",
            "answer": "<p><strong>ERGO</strong> is Bahco's ergonomic handle design system, developed from 1983 and scientifically validated in 1996. It uses a three-component handle construction that reduces hand fatigue, increases torque transfer and helps prevent repetitive strain injuries. The core principle is that you should never have to adapt your hands to a tool — the tool adapts to you.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_3": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What warranty do Bahco hand tools carry?",
            "answer": "<p>Bahco hand tools carry a <strong>lifetime warranty</strong> against defects in workmanship and materials for the usable life of the product. If a Bahco tool fails under normal professional use, contact us and we will arrange a replacement. As an official UK stockist, Invicta Tools can process warranty claims directly.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_4": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Who makes Bahco tools?",
            "answer": "<p>Bahco is the premium brand of <strong>SNA Europe</strong>, formed in 2005 from the merger of Bahco AB and Herramientas Eurotools S.A. The brand traces its origins to Johan Petter Johansson's smithy in Enk\u00f6ping, Sweden in 1886. SNA Europe is now part of the Snap-on Incorporated group.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_5": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Are Bahco tools suitable for professional trade use?",
            "answer": "<p>Absolutely. Bahco tools are designed exclusively for professional use. The entire range — from adjustable wrenches and pliers to hacksaws, socket sets and torque tools — is engineered to withstand daily trade use. The ERGO range is specifically designed for tradespeople who use hand tools all day, every day.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_6": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Do you offer trade pricing on Bahco?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. We offer <strong>competitive trade pricing</strong> across the full Bahco range. Contact our trade team on <strong>01843 593 440</strong> or email <strong>sales@invictatools.co.uk</strong> for volume discounts and trade account enquiries. We also provide free next-day delivery on all orders over \u00a399.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
